{"lemma":"حاشِيَةٌ","slug":"حاشِيَةٌ","root":"ح.ش.#","root_slug":"ح-ش-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ش-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8143","n8160"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"edge, rim, border"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hem"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"marginal note"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"appendix"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"supplement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"postscript"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"digression"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"region, tract"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shade, protection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attendants","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8143","headword_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ","root":"H$w","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and its dual and pl.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$owN","text_ar":"حَشْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places. ―         -b2-  See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n8160","headword_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ","root":"H$Y","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selvage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selvedge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of the two sides that have no unwoven extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of the two long sides that have at their two ends the unwoven threads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) of a garment, or piece of cloth: (S, T, M, Mgh, Msb, K:) and in like manner, of other things; (K, TA;) as, for instance, (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tract of herbage, and of the mirage; and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAm","text_ar":"مَقَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAm A_ibor`hiym","text_ar":"مَقَام اـِبْرٰهِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Temple of Mekkeh]: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaA$K","text_ar":"حَوَاشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"margin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a book or writing. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A writing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writings, upon the margin"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"margins"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a book:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a marginal note,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marginal notes; an annotation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a comment, scholium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gloss:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a series of annotations, comments, scholia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glosses; a commentary on particular words and passages of a book;"},{"kind":"text","text":"distinguished from a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroH","text_ar":"شَرْح"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is an exposition, explanation, or interpretation, in the form of a running commentary, comprising the entire text of the work which it expounds.] ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An indefinite portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of property, or of cattle: (Msb:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion from the side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not selected: for, accord. to some,] the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o mino HawaA$iY","text_ar":"خُذْ مِنْ حَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amowaAlihimo","text_ar":"اَمْوَالِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou from the sides of their collections of cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for the poor-rate,] without choosing [the best]: this meaning being from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyap","text_ar":"حَاشِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used in relation to a garment, or piece of cloth, meaning the \"side.\" (Mgh. [But see another explanation of this saying voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$owN","text_ar":"حَشْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN Aln~asabi","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ النَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The collateral relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations; such as the paternal uncle, and his son:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HA$yp","text_ar":"حاشية"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the “ side. ” of a garment, or piece of cloth. (Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapu","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulK","text_ar":"رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man's family and dependents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who are under his protection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its dual and pl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$owN","text_ar":"حَشْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places. ―         -b8-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$FY","text_ar":"حَشًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the present art.), last sentence but one. ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN raqiyqN AlHawaA$iY","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ رَقِيقٌ الحَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man gentle, gracious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courteous, to his associates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N raqiyqu AlHawaA$iY","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ رَقِيقُ الحَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plentiful, easy, life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamoEN kaviyfu AlHawaA$iY","text_ar":"جَمْعٌ كَثِيفُ الحَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A congregated body crowding close together, side against side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 294.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","M","T","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}